summaries.title: Building Inclusive Engineering Teams
summaries.summaryText: Ethan noted that successful project outcomes often came from teams with diverse backgrounds and perspectives. He believes empathy and active listening should be core engineering competencies. [Part 3/4]

summaries.title: Representation and Visibility in Engineering Spaces
summaries.summaryText: She emphasized how few Black women were visible in faculty and leadership roles, describing representation as both motivating and emotionally taxing. Her NSBE involvement offered vital affirmation and a platform to advocate for equity. [Part 3/4]

summaries.title: Navigating Gender Bias in Research Environments
summaries.summaryText: She recounted experiences where her technical contributions were overlooked and strategies she used to assert confidence. [Part 3/4]

summaries.title: Transition from High School to University-Level Engineering
summaries.summaryText: Luis found the shift from project-based high school learning to theory-heavy coursework challenging but rewarding. [Part 1/4]

themes.title: Mentorship Networks as Retention Mechanisms
themes.description: Mentorship emerges as a consistent strategy for increasing belonging and persistence for students from marginalized groups. Aaliyah’s mentorship program demonstrates how peer-led initiatives can fill institutional gaps. [Extended 2]

themes.title: Family Expectations and Cultural Motivation
themes.description: Cultural values around family honor and sacrifice serve both as motivation and a source of pressure for first-generation Vietnamese-American students pursuing STEM. [Extended 2]

themes.title: Sense of Belonging in STEM for Students of Color
themes.description: Maria’s reflections highlight how peer representation and visibility in classrooms significantly influence belonging and persistence for Latina women in engineering. [Extended 1]

themes.title: Navigating Institutional Barriers as a First-Generation Student
themes.description: First-generation identity shapes how Maria interprets bureaucratic and academic systems, creating additional cognitive and emotional labor compared to continuing-generation peers. [Extended 1]

themes.title: Team Diversity as an Engineering Strength
themes.description: Ethan believes interdisciplinary and culturally diverse teams drive better innovation outcomes, reflecting the growing importance of social awareness in engineering practice. [Extended 2]

themes.title: Navigating Institutional Barriers as a First-Generation Student
themes.description: First-generation identity shapes how Maria interprets bureaucratic and academic systems, creating additional cognitive and emotional labor compared to continuing-generation peers. [Extended 4]

themes.title: Peer Mentorship as a Belonging Intervention
themes.description: Daniel emphasized how structured mentorship programs provided psychological safety and belonging cues, normalizing struggle and improving persistence among marginalized students. [Extended 2]

themes.title: Cultural Representation as a Source of Motivation
themes.description: Seeing Latino professionals at SHPE events reinforced Maria’s sense of purpose and belonging in a field where representation remains limited. [Extended 1]

areasForImprovement.title: Increase Cultural Representation in Engineering Programs
areasForImprovement.description: Students emphasized the importance of seeing role models and mentors from similar cultural backgrounds. Faculty partnerships with student cultural organizations could foster inclusion and belonging. [Extended 2]
actionItems: Integrate cultural competence into departmental events

areasForImprovement.title: Expand Visibility of First-Gen Student Resources
areasForImprovement.description: Current communication about financial aid, academic advising, and mentorship resources does not adequately reach first-generation students. Improving targeted outreach through orientation and department emails could reduce inequities in access to support. [Extended 2]
actionItems: Add first-gen resource links to department portals

areasForImprovement.title: Expand Peer Mentoring for First-Generation STEM Students
areasForImprovement.description: Formalize mentoring programs that pair upperclassmen with first-generation students early in their academic journey. These networks reduce imposter syndrome and improve retention rates. [Extended 4]
actionItems: Create opt-in mentoring tracks for first-gen students
Provide mentor training focused on inclusive communication

areasForImprovement.title: Formal Recognition for Student Advocacy and Mentorship Work
areasForImprovement.description: Students like Aaliyah contribute substantial unpaid labor in mentoring and advocacy roles. Institutions should recognize these contributions as part of leadership and service learning frameworks. [Extended 1]
actionItems: Create service-learning credit for mentorship and advocacy roles
Include advocacy experience in leadership award criteria

areasForImprovement.title: Integrate Wellness Programming into STEM Curriculum
areasForImprovement.description: Develop optional workshops or credit modules linking mental health and STEM performance. [Extended 3]

areasForImprovement.title: Enhance First-Gen Orientation Programs
areasForImprovement.description: Provide stronger academic transition support for first-generation students entering engineering. [Extended 2]
